descp2: A `Tensor` representing audio data with shape `[k, t, c]`, where `k` is the number of audio clips, `t` is the number of frames, and `c` is the number of channels. Elements should be floating-point values in `[-1.0, 1.0]`. Any of the dimensions may be statically unknown (i.e., `None`).
